==Portuguese==

===Pronunciation===
*/aˈve(x)/

===Etymology===
Latin [[habere]].

===Auxiliary verb===
'''haver'''
# 'to have'; an auxiliary used for various purposes, for example, to make some future (similar to English 'have to') and perfect ('have done') tenses.
#:''Amanhã '''hei''' de ver o filme.''
#::I will see the movie tomorrow.

===Verb===
'''haver'''
# There is, there are.
#:'''''Há''' um banco aqui perto.''
#: There is a bank nearby.

